namedLocations.description: Gujarat (/ˌɡʊdʒəˈrɑːt/, Gujarati: [ˈɡudʒəɾɑt] ) is a state on the western coast of India with a coastline of 1,600 km (990 mi) – most of which lies on the Kathiawar peninsula – and a population in excess of 60 million. It is the sixth largest Indian state by area and the ninth largest state by population. Gujarat is bordered by Rajasthan to the northeast, Daman and Diu to the south, Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Maharashtra to the southeast, Madhya Pradesh to the east, and the Arabian Sea and the Pakistani province of Sindh to the west. Its capital city is Gandhinagar, while its largest city is Ahmedabad. The Gujarati-speaking people of India are indigenous to the state. The economy of Gujarat is the fifth-largest state economy in India with ₹14.96 lakh crore (US$220 billion) in gross domestic product and a per capita GDP of ₹157,000 (US$2,300). Gujarat ranks fifteenth among Indian states in human development index.

transcript.text: Hello, welcome to Anpin Shop.
In this video we will learn about how to set up the sidebar.
Let's talk about key features and benefits.
Sidebar exist on almost every page of the website which affects the overall customer experience.
It also plays a great role in the website when navigation what user clicks on and how long they stay on the website.
Sidebars helps visitors in accessing the information quickly.
You can use the given interface to enable disable sections on the right sidebar or left sidebar.
Let's have a look into the admin.
First of all, we need to go to store precision.
Click on sidebar management.
Using the given interface, we have given options to enable or disable sections on the right sidebar and left sidebar.
From the icons next to each drop down, you can choose which items to hide under the sections and save it.
When we go to storefront, you can see the sidebar it's enabled.
Also, with each section we have given a brief description stating which URL are included into the same.
Next we have sidebar widget.
Every widget on your sidebars allows your website visitors to interact well with your websites, services and features.
Widgets aim to fulfill your conversion goals for each specific page.
For example, if you want to show Contact Us detail section listing on the left sidebar, you have to go to edit.
Here you need to change the position from right side to the left sidebar and here you can save it.
So when you go to the front here, you can see on the product page it's showing contact us details on the left hand sidebar.
So in this way, you can manage your sidebars on your website.
Thank you for watching this video.
In case of any further queries or concern, you can connect to us.
Thank you.
